|rev5 = [[New York Post]]
|rev5score = {{Rating|3|3}}<ref>[http://www.nypost.com/p/entertainment/that_the_ticket_2rv41tCxkyTuUAmIUAIRrM New York Post review]</ref>
}}<!-- Automatically generated by DASHBot-->
The album was generally well received, with [[Allmusic]] giving it a 3.5/5 rating stating "The sound? By-the-numbers Los Angeles metal with slight post-grunge updates. "Shut the F*** Up" draws on Generation Swine-era Cr<U+00FC>e, while "I Got a Gun" reaches eagerly for classic Queensr<U+00FF>che. The Brides play well as a unit, and LeGrand makes up for his lack of nuance with power.".<ref>[{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r677339|pure_url=yes}} allmusic ((( Here Come The Brides > Overview)))]</ref> [[Rolling Stone]] gave the album 3 out of 5 stars saying " Singer London Le Grand works a fine Bowie-Axl yowl, but he mostly gets points for his great porn-metal name. Throughout, Brides show today's whippersnappers how to deliver real cock-rock shock - even the de rigueur power ballad "Only Get So Far" has cojones.".<ref>[http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/bridesofdestruction/albums/album/5171317/review/5943440/here_come_the_brides Brides of Destruction: Here Come The Brides : Music Reviews : Rolling Stone]</ref> [[Blabbermouth]] gave a more mixed review stating "the record <U+2014> a compact nine-song effort <U+2014> only provides sporadic moments of inspiration and little in the way of truly electrifying rock and roll. It's commendable that Sixx, Guns, drummer Scot Coogan, and vocalist London LeGrand are sticking their middle fingers at trends and doing what they want musically, but the shopworn selection of material here generates very few real sparks."<ref>[http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/showreview.aspx?reviewID=163 BRIDES OF DESTRUCTION Here Come The Brides (Sanctuary)]</ref>

